HEADWORD: Depectible
<hw>De*pec"ti*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>depectere</ets> to comb off; <ets>de-</ets> + <ets>pectere</ets> to
comb.]</ety> <def>Tough; thick; capable of extension.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Some bodies are of a more <qex>depectible</qex> nature than
oil.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Depeculation</ent>⟦br⟧
